HEADWORD: hypercube
<hw>hypercube</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A mathematical object existing in
more than three dimensions, analogous to the cube in that each
two-dimensional facet of the surface is a square; a generalization of a
cube in more than three dimensions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hyperdicrotic</ent>⟦br⟧
